module.exports = {"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Jeffry.in","author":"Jeff Wainwright"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"/Users/jwainwright/Dropbox/me/git-docs/yowainwright.github.io/src/pages/2017-05-07-week-17-17.md absPath of file >>> MarkdownRemark","html":"<p>While skateboarding hard during my young adult life, my ankles were not treated the best. Now, well into my thirties, I sometimes have extended ankle problems after minor injuries—like stubbing my foot. This happened this week, so I wasn’t able to do much exercise. At work, I built an observer to try to fix a race condition we’ve been dealing with in our analytics tool since before I started. Today, Sunday, my ankle felt good enough that I could go on a long walk and I did—in the snow, just above Los Angeles.</p>\n<figure>\n  <img src=\"https://yowainwright.imgix.net/wk-17/portrait.jpg?w=800&amp;h=800&amp;crop=focalpoint&amp;auto=format\" alt=\"Ruby Beach\">\n</figure>","frontmatter":{"featured_image":null,"meta":"Week 17, I was dealing with an ankle injury and using an observer to fix race conditions","title":"Week 17, dealing with an ankle injury and using an observer and/or a mediator pattern","date":"May 07, 2017","path":"/week-17-17/"}}},"pathContext":{"path":"/week-17-17/","_PARENT":"SOURCE"}}


